 What Is Xanadu Prime?
Xanadu Prime is the public‑facing layer of Project Xanadu — a long‑term initiative to build a stable, transparent, and interoperable knowledge substrate.
Prime is the interface; the Xi substrate is the machinery underneath.

For the architectural view, see Prime‑Era Overview.

Why It Exists
People drown in information but starve for structure.
Prime solves three universal failure modes:

Information Drift — meaning decays over time

Context Loss — documents lose their “why”

Lineage Breaks — authorship and history disappear

Prime provides stable naming, explicit provenance, and coherent structure so knowledge stays intact.

See Provenance Timeline.

